Biel  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Reszel, within Kętrzyn County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  west of Reszel,  west of Kętrzyn, and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
